description:
&lt;p&gt;Cygnet Health Care have been providing a national network of high quality specialist mental health services for more than 30 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Located in south-east London, Cygnet Hospital Blackheath provides inpatient low secure and PICU services for men with a mental health illness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently recruiting a full time support worker for Meridian Ward, our low secure service which can support up to 16 men. The ward aims to balance the needs of therapy and security whilst helping prepare service users to lead full and independent lives in the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an active member of our dynamic team, you’ll provide support for our nursing staff including the admission, assessment, implementation and discharge of inpatients, with a focus on dignity and safety at all times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role you’ll:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Offer enhanced care with a flexible learning approach for all our patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in the hospital area, providing guidance and encouragement to patients through physical and emotional support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a safe, clean and enjoyable environment to live and work in&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist patients with their medical and welfare needs and report as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safeguard patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn about individuals’ specific needs and provide help in the most appropriate way&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;re looking for people who have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in an inpatient, hospital setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced with challenging behaviours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills and the ability to be a good team player&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The sensitivity and energy required to provide a trusting, stimulating and varied lifestyle for the patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A genuine desire to make a real difference in people’s lives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong, flexible mental aptitude and an ability to cope with the physical demands of the role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility to work shifts patterns on a rata basisin including nights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NVQ level 2 in a relevant care setting is preferable but not essential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In return, you’ll receive a competitive salary and a range of benefits including:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full training and Induction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;£3,000 London location allowance (London weighting)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regular coaching and support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Discount Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company paid Life Assurance scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Smart Health Toolkit- Providing you with Fitness Programmes, Nutrition consultation and Health checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health Cash Plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Subsidised meals on duty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note: successful candidates will be required to undergo an enhanced DBS check.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
